<br>
There are a huge number of encounters in this game, even the same mob done twice won't be the exact same both times.<br>
<br>
If you are talking in terms of damage, it's &quot;roughly&quot; like this:<br>
<br>
The maximum dps for a nuker is limited ultimately by the cast times of his spells and his luck with crits.  This ceiling can be lowered by a mob that forces the wizard to waste time(for instance Wuoshi or a Quad-kite).<br>
<br>
In most situations, the chance of drawing aggro also reduces your rate of damage.<br>
<br>
Once he runs out of mana, his dps will slow down further.<br>
<br>
However, in order for dps to slow as a result of mana loss, conditions must be met:<br>
<br>
1.  Mana expenditure must be greater than mana income.<br>
2.  The &quot;critical time&quot; must be greater than manapool/defecit.<br>
<br>
Note that for many encounters, &quot;critical time&quot; depends not only on the mob but also on the capabilities of your group or raid.<br>
<br>
For a quick example, lets take a fight where a wizard can spend 150 mana per tick, and the fight lasts 4 minutes(40 ticks).  Lets say he has a 4800point mana pool.  You need 6000 mana total for the fight.  1200 has to come from somewhere other than your normal mana pool.  1200 over 4 minutes is a mere 30 mana per tick.  Any mana regen over 30 is pretty much wasted, you'll end the fight with mana you were unable to spend.  This is actually one of the remaining uses of manaburn-- to dump mana that would have otherwise been wasted. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<br>Err, Forum Arch Mage?</span><br>  Posts: 3586<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/19/03 1:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The High End Wizard</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Even so, based on the other thread where I was smacked down pretty hard<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Where is this other thread?  You seem to be attacking something of a straw man or invisible man here...  No one here is saying FT is never useful. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dlaren4444>dlaren4444</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 586<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/19/03 5:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The High End Wizard</span><hr size=1>  Nice discussion guys, disagreement with no one insulting anyone.<br>
