Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sincrofashad>SincroFashad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/19/03 1:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The High End Wizard</span><hr size=1> Here's the thread I referenced.  Its on page three, so no need to bump it back to the top.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=25359.topic">pub140.ezboard.com/fgraff...5359.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Personally, I would first have to be convinced that such a disparity exists. But in any case:<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
My guild has multiple casters at or near the worn FT cap and at the same time possesses a single Vengeance item, which was acquired from Aerin`Dar.  We do have access to additional Veng items from the ornate armor drops in places like BoT, but we've been fairly unlucky, and haven't gotten a single one yet as a guild, and we've been in BoT since Early December at least.  The facts of the matter are, however: We could progress no further as a guild, and put virtually every caster at the worn FT cap, but no melee would come close to approaching the worn ATK cap.<br>
<br>
To answer your questions about when would I either look back and say Vengeance did nothing for me, or think going into the fight, my gear doesn't mean crap, there's only one fight my guild has currently handled where Vengeance would be wasted for me, and that's Cursed in Ssra.  Thus, you are correct, only fights where I am relegated to ranged combat only.  Not a big issue for me at this time.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
In some situations, FT is more useful than Vengeance, other situations Vengeance is clearly superior.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
FT being superior in any non-combat situation, Vengeance being superior in any combat situation where the melee (not rangers) are relegated to ranged combat.  That statement almost sounds like an absolute, though, and those tend to get proved wrong at some point.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Ssra/Tier 2-3 plane guilds are not the ones being discussed by the original poster, and Ssra/Tier 2-3 casters probably won't generally have gobs of FT. Flowing Thought comes in greatest quantities from Vex Thal. 6-10 can probably be achieved by normal ssra-level casters, but don't forget Aura of Battle items-- those give +ATK. Casters also still don't have an &quot;equivalent&quot; to primal weapons.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Unfortunately, guilds at my level can and do have gobs of FT items.  There's more of it available then you think.  Aura of Battle stuff is available to us, but again, not in the amounts FT is.  Not meant to be a whine, just stating a fact.  For casters lacking a 'primal weapon' equivalent, you're right.  I can't think of any item that gives a worn or procced effect of: causes all spells cast to be resisted at -50.  Damn, that would be cool, though.<br>
<br>
I wasn't trying to be pouty.  Shut up and color is sorta a military phrase for: Nothing further to be gained by arguing a point into senselessness, lets move on.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Again though, you can't just say FT adds X DPS because it just doesn't work that way. If I fight once an hour and don't go OOM, FT has essentially no effect. Compare that to melee that picks up a better weapon or Vengeance items. Those do have an effect, even if you only fight once an hour.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
